@node FIRST " SuperLeagueV3.51 Guide - Before you load up "

@{b}The First Thing You Should Do :@{ub}

   @{b}BACK UP THIS DISK!@{ub} By the very nature of the program, you will
be making frequent writes to disk, as you store the league data. You should
backup this disk, before you even use SuperLeague, just in case something
goes badly wrong with the file structure. (Accidental deletion of important
files or read/write errors in particular)

   Ensure that your machine meets the necessary @{" System Requirements " link SPEC} to
load SuperLeagueV3.51.

@{b}Important Note regarding usage :@{ub} 
	
   Due to the comprehensive amount of data stored by SuperLeague V3.51,
a delicate data storage structure exists for each league processed. This
entails 7 major files for EVERY league you set up, in different directories.
If just one of those files were to go wrong in any way (Accidental deletion,
read/write errors etc) then it is very likely that that league becomes 
unusable. I should point out that if you go about TRYING to crash this
software by messing about with the data files, or their contents then you 
may well succeed. SuperLeague will not crash in circumstances in which the
user is behaving responsibly and does not manipulate the @{"System Datafiles " link DATAFILES}
from the shell/Cli.
@endnode
@node SPEC " SuperLeagueV3.51 System Requirements "
@{b}SuperLeague V3.51 system requirements :@{ub}
	
	Computer : 	Any Amiga (A500,A500+,A600,A1200,A2000,A3000,A4000)
	O/S Version :	Kickstart 1.3 or upwards
	Memory :	1MB minimum
	Drives : 	Any number of drives

@{b}Backward-Compatability with Previous releases of Superleague :@{ub}

	SuperLeague V3.51 files are compatable with all previous @{"versions" link HISTORY}
of the program (V3.40,V3.41,V3.50 for example). However they are not 
compatable with the new version @{"SuperLeague V4.01" link UPGRADE} because it features
an entirely new data storage method.
@endnode
